🧭 1. Basic Navigation Commands

pwd — Print working directory

ls — List directory contents

cd — Change directory

cd .. — Go up one directory

cd ~ — Go to home directory

ls -l — Long listing format

ls -a — Show hidden files

tree — Display directory structure

find — Search for files

locate — Quickly locate files

📂 2. File and Directory Management

mkdir — Create a directory

rmdir — Remove empty directory

rm -r — Remove directory recursively

cp — Copy files or directories

mv — Move or rename files

touch — Create an empty file

cat — View file contents

less — View large files one page at a time

head — Show first lines of a file

tail — Show last lines of a file

🛠️ 3. File Operations & Permissions

chmod — Change file permissions

chown — Change file owner

chgrp — Change group ownership

stat — Show file details

file — Identify file type

ln — Create hard link

ln -s — Create symbolic (soft) link

diff — Compare files

cmp — Compare binary files

wc — Count words, lines, and characters

🔍 4. Searching & Filtering

grep — Search text in files

egrep — Extended grep (regex support)

fgrep — Fixed string grep

find . -name "*.txt" — Find all .txt files

sort — Sort file lines

uniq — Filter duplicate lines

cut — Cut specific columns from text

awk — Pattern scanning and processing

sed — Stream editor for text replacement

xargs — Build and execute command lines

⚙️ 5. System Information

uname -a — Show system info

hostname — Display hostname

uptime — Show system uptime

whoami — Display current user

date — Show current date/time

cal — Display calendar

df -h — Show disk usage

du -sh — Show folder size

top — Display running processes

htop — Interactive process viewer

🧮 6. Process Management

ps — Show running processes

ps aux — Detailed process list

kill — Kill process by PID

killall — Kill all processes by name

bg — Resume a job in background

fg — Bring job to foreground

jobs — Show active jobs

nice — Set process priority

renice — Change priority of running process

pgrep — Find process by name

🌐 7. Network Commands

ping — Test network connection

ifconfig — Show network interfaces

ip a — Modern alternative to ifconfig

netstat -tuln — Show open ports

ss -tuln — Modern socket statistics

curl — Fetch data from URL

wget — Download files from web

scp — Securely copy files between systems

ssh — Secure shell login

traceroute — Show route packets take

🧑‍💻 8. User Management

adduser — Create new user

userdel — Delete user

passwd — Change password

su — Switch user

sudo — Run command as superuser

who — Show logged-in users

last — Show login history

id — Show user ID and groups

groups — List user’s groups

finger — Display user info

📦 9. Package Management

(Varies by distro)
81. apt update — Refresh package list (Debian/Ubuntu)
82. apt upgrade — Upgrade installed packages
83. apt install — Install new package
84. apt remove — Remove package
85. apt search — Search for package
86. yum install — Install package (RHEL/CentOS)
87. dnf update — Fedora package update
88. snap install — Install snap package
89. flatpak install — Install flatpak app
90. brew install — Install package (Homebrew)

🧾 10. Compression & Archiving

tar -cvf — Create tar archive

tar -xvf — Extract tar archive

gzip — Compress file

gunzip — Decompress gzip

zip — Create zip file

unzip — Extract zip file

bzip2 — Compress using bzip2

xz — Compress using xz

7z — 7-zip archiver

rsync — Sync files and directories

🔁 11. Miscellaneous

history — Show command history

alias — Create command shortcuts

unalias — Remove alias

clear — Clear terminal screen

echo — Print message to screen

env — Show environment variables

export — Set environment variable

time — Measure command execution time

sleep — Pause for seconds

man — Display manual page
